name: Entity
description: PlayFab Entity APIs provide a variety of core PlayFab features and work consistently across a broad set of entities, such as titles, players, characters, and more. API methods for executing CloudScript with an Entity Profile

properties.description: New version of the role data.

properties.name: SetResult
properties.description: Indicates which operation was completed, either Created, Updated, Deleted or None.

properties.name: Events
properties.description: Collection of events to write to PlayStream.

properties.name: AssignedEventIds
properties.description: The unique identifiers assigned by the server to the events, in the same order as the events in the request. Only returned if FlushToPlayStream option is true.

calls.name: AbortFileUploads
calls.summary: Abort pending file uploads to an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Aborts the pending upload of the requested files.

calls.name: AcceptGroupApplication
calls.summary: Accepts an outstanding invitation to to join a group
calls.requestDetails: Accepts an outstanding invitation to to join a group if the invited entity is not blocked by the group. Nothing is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: AcceptGroupInvitation
calls.summary: Accepts an invitation to join a group
calls.requestDetails: Accepts an outstanding invitation to join the group if the invited entity is not blocked by the group. Only the invited entity or a parent in its chain (e.g. title) may accept the invitation on the invited entity's behalf. Nothing is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: AddMembers
calls.summary: Adds members to a group or role.
calls.requestDetails: Adds members to a group or role. Existing members of the group will added to roles within the group, but if the user is not already a member of the group, only title claimants may add them to the group, and others must use the group application or invite system to add new members to a group. Returns nothing if successful.

calls.name: ApplyToGroup
calls.summary: Applies to join a group
calls.requestDetails: Creates an application to join a group. Calling this while a group application already exists will return the same application instead of an error and will not refresh the time before the application expires. By default, if the entity has an invitation to join the group outstanding, this will accept the invitation to join the group instead and return an error indicating such, rather than creating a duplicate application to join that will need to be cleaned up later. Returns information about the application or an error indicating an invitation was accepted instead.

calls.name: BlockEntity
calls.summary: Blocks a list of entities from joining a group.
calls.requestDetails: Blocks a list of entities from joining a group. Blocked entities may not create new applications to join, be invited to join, accept an invitation, or have an application accepted. Failure due to being blocked does not clean up existing applications or invitations to the group. No data is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: CancelMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Cancel a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Users can cancel a matchmaking ticket at anytime. Anyone in the matchmaking ticket can cancel         it. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket because the players         must consent to enter matchmaking again after the cancellation which is the         same as creating a new ticket.         The ticket can be in different states when it is cancelled:         * The ticket has not started matching because not everyone has joined the ticket.          If the ticket is cancelled, it will be deleted and never match.         * The ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching          and it will be deleted.         * The ticket has been matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled.         There may be race conditions due to latency between the ticket being matched and         the client being notified the match is ready. The client must handle the possibility         that the cancel request may fail if the match has been made but the notification         has not arrived.

calls.name: ChangeMemberRole
calls.summary: Changes the role membership of a list of entities from one role to another.
calls.requestDetails: Changes the role membership of a list of entities from one role to another in in a single operation. The destination role must already exist. This is equivalent to adding the entities to the destination role and removing from the origin role. Returns nothing if successful.

calls.name: CreateGroup
calls.summary: Creates a new group.
calls.requestDetails: Creates a new group, as well as administration and member roles, based off of a title's group template. Returns information about the group that was created.

calls.name: CreateMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Create a matchmaking ticket as a client.
calls.requestDetails: The client specifies the creator's attributes and optionally a list of other users to match with.

calls.name: CreateRole
calls.summary: Creates a new group role.
calls.requestDetails: Creates a new role within an existing group, with no members. Both the role ID and role name must be unique within the group, but the name can be the same as the ID. The role ID is set at creation and cannot be changed. Returns information about the role that was created.

calls.name: CreateServerMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Create a matchmaking ticket as a server.
calls.requestDetails: The server specifies all the creators and their attributes.

calls.name: DeleteFiles
calls.summary: Delete files on an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Deletes the requested files from the entity's profile.

calls.name: DeleteGroup
calls.summary: Deletes a group and all roles, invitations, join requests, and blocks associated with it.
calls.requestDetails: Deletes a group and all roles, invitations, join requests, and blocks associated with it. Permission to delete is only required the group itself to execute this action. The group and data cannot be cannot be recovered once removed, but any abuse reports about the group will remain. No data is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: DeleteRole
calls.summary: Deletes an existing role in a group.
calls.requestDetails: Returns information about the role

calls.name: ExecuteEntityCloudScript
calls.summary: Executes CloudScript using the Entity Profile
calls.requestDetails: Executes CloudScript with the entity profile that is defined in the request.

calls.name: FinalizeFileUploads
calls.summary: Finalize file uploads to an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Finalizes the upload of the requested files. Verifies that the files have been successfully uploaded and moves the file pointers from pending to live.

calls.name: GetEntityToken
calls.summary: Method to exchange a legacy AuthenticationTicket or title SecretKey for an Entity Token or to refresh a still valid Entity Token.
calls.requestDetails: This API must be called with X-SecretKey, X-Authentication or X-EntityToken headers. An optional EntityKey may be included to attempt to set the resulting EntityToken to a specific entity, however the entity must be a relation of the caller, such as the master_player_account of a character. If sending X-EntityToken the account will be marked as freshly logged in and will issue a new token. If using X-Authentication or X-EntityToken the header must still be valid and cannot be expired or revoked.

calls.name: GetFiles
calls.summary: Retrieves file metadata from an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Returns URLs that may be used to download the files for a profile for a limited length of time. Only returns files that have been successfully uploaded, files that are still pending will either return the old value, if it exists, or nothing.

calls.name: GetGlobalPolicy
calls.summary: Gets the global title access policy
calls.requestDetails: Retrieves the title access policy that is used before the profile's policy is inspected during a request. If never customized this will return the default starter policy built by PlayFab.

calls.name: GetGroup
calls.summary: Gets information about a group and its roles
calls.requestDetails: Returns the ID, name, role list and other non-membership related information about a group.

calls.name: GetMatch
calls.summary: Get a match.
calls.requestDetails: When matchmaking has successfully matched together a collection of         tickets, it produces a 'match' with an ID. The match contains all of         the players that were matched together, server connection information,         etc. The match ID is usually sent to the matched players using the         activity service.         Only the players in the original ticket can get the match.

calls.name: GetMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Get a matchmaking ticket by ticket ID.
calls.requestDetails: The ticket includes the players who have joined, their attributes,         who still hasn't joined, etc. Only the ticket creator and invited players can get the ticket.

calls.name: GetObjects
calls.summary: Retrieves objects from an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Gets JSON objects from an entity profile and returns it.

calls.name: GetProfile
calls.summary: Retrieves the entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity type and entity identifier will retrieve the profile from the entity store. If the profile being retrieved is the caller's, then the read operation is consistent, if not it is an inconsistent read. An inconsistent read means that we do not guarantee all committed writes have occurred before reading the profile, allowing for a stale read. If consistency is important the Version Number on the result can be used to compare which version of the profile any reader has.

calls.name: GetProfiles
calls.summary: Retrieves the entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Given a set of entity types and entity identifiers will retrieve all readable profiles properties for the caller. Profiles that the caller is not allowed to read will silently not be included in the results.

calls.name: InitiateFileUploads
calls.summary: Initiates file uploads to an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Returns URLs that may be used to upload the files for a profile 5 minutes. After using the upload calls FinalizeFileUploads must be called to move the file status from pending to live.

calls.name: InviteToGroup
calls.summary: Invites a player to join a group
calls.requestDetails: Invites a player to join a group, if they are not blocked by the group. An optional role can be provided to automatically assign the player to the role if they accept the invitation. By default, if the entity has an application to the group outstanding, this will accept the application instead and return an error indicating such, rather than creating a duplicate invitation to join that will need to be cleaned up later. Returns information about the new invitation or an error indicating an existing application to join was accepted.

calls.name: IsMember
calls.summary: Checks to see if an entity is a member of a group or role within the group
calls.requestDetails: Checks to see if an entity is a member of a group or role within the group. A result indicating if the entity is a member of the group is returned, or a permission error if the caller does not have permission to read the group's member list.

calls.name: JoinMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Join a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Add the user to a matchmaking ticket and specify all the user's matchmaking         attributes. Users can only join a ticket if and only if they were 'invited'         to join the ticket by the ticket creator in the CreateMatchmakingTicket         call.         The matchmaking service automatically starts matching the ticket against         other matchmaking tickets once all players have joined the ticket. Therefore,         it is not possible to join a ticket once it has started matching.

calls.name: ListGroupApplications
calls.summary: Lists all outstanding requests to join a group
calls.requestDetails: Lists all outstanding requests to join a group. Returns a list of all requests to join, as well as when the request will expire. To get the group applications for a specific entity, use ListMembershipOpportunities.

calls.name: ListGroupBlocks
calls.summary: Lists all entities blocked from joining a group
calls.requestDetails: Lists all entities blocked from joining a group. A list of blocked entities is returned

calls.name: ListGroupInvitations
calls.summary: Lists all outstanding invitations for a group
calls.requestDetails: Lists all outstanding invitations for a group. Returns a list of entities that have been invited, as well as when the invitation will expire. To get the group invitations for a specific entity, use ListMembershipOpportunities.

calls.name: ListGroupMembers
calls.summary: Lists all members for a group
calls.requestDetails: Gets a list of members and the roles they belong to within the group. If the caller does not have permission to view the role, and the member is in no other role, the member is not displayed. Returns a list of entities that are members of the group.

calls.name: ListMembership
calls.summary: Lists all groups and roles for an entity
calls.requestDetails: Lists the groups and roles that an entity is a part of, checking to see if group and role metadata and memberships should be visible to the caller. If the entity is not in any roles that are visible to the caller, the group is not returned in the results, even if the caller otherwise has permission to see that the entity is a member of that group.

calls.name: ListMembershipOpportunities
calls.summary: Lists all outstanding invitations and group applications for an entity
calls.requestDetails: Lists all outstanding group applications and invitations for an entity. Anyone may call this for any entity, but data will only be returned for the entity or a parent of that entity. To list invitations or applications for a group to check if a player is trying to join, use ListGroupInvitations and ListGroupApplications.

calls.name: RemoveGroupApplication
calls.summary: Removes an application to join a group
calls.requestDetails: Removes an existing application to join the group. This is used for both rejection of an application as well as withdrawing an application. The applying entity or a parent in its chain (e.g. title) may withdraw the application, and any caller with appropriate access in the group may reject an application. No data is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: RemoveGroupInvitation
calls.summary: Removes an invitation join a group
calls.requestDetails: Removes an existing invitation to join the group. This is used for both rejection of an invitation as well as rescinding an invitation. The invited entity or a parent in its chain (e.g. title) may reject the invitation by calling this method, and any caller with appropriate access in the group may rescind an invitation. No data is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: RemoveMembers
calls.summary: Removes members from a group.
calls.requestDetails: Removes members from a group. A member can always remove themselves from a group, regardless of permissions. Returns nothing if successful.

calls.name: SetGlobalPolicy
calls.summary: Sets the global title access policy
calls.requestDetails: Updates the title access policy that is used before the profile's policy is inspected during a request. Policies are compiled and cached for several minutes so an update here may not be reflected in behavior for a short time.

calls.name: SetObjects
calls.summary: Sets objects on an entity's profile.
calls.requestDetails: Sets JSON objects on the requested entity profile. May include a version number to be used to perform optimistic concurrency operations during update. If the current version differs from the version in the request the request will be ignored. If no version is set on the request then the value will always be updated if the values differ. Using the version value does not guarantee a write though, ConcurrentEditError may still occur if multiple clients are attempting to update the same profile.

calls.name: SetProfilePolicy
calls.summary: Sets the profiles access policy
calls.requestDetails: This will set the access policy statements on the given entity profile. This is not additive, any existing statements will be replaced with the statements in this request.

calls.name: UnblockEntity
calls.summary: Unblocks a list of entities from joining a group
calls.requestDetails: Unblocks a list of entities from joining a group. No data is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: UpdateGroup
calls.summary: Updates non-membership data about a group.
calls.requestDetails: Updates data about a group, such as the name or default member role. Returns information about whether the update was successful. Only title claimants may modify the administration role for a group.

calls.name: UpdateRole
calls.summary: Updates metadata about a role.
calls.requestDetails: Updates the role name. Returns information about whether the update was successful.

calls.name: WriteEvents
calls.summary: Writes events to PlayStream.
